aarinen to design the tulip chair for production in  the company was accorded exclusive manufacturing and sales rights to ludwig mies van der rohe furniture including the barcelona chair designed for the  barcelona pavilion  the company holds production rights to the wassily chair by marcel breuer in  knoll acquired exclusive us production rights of the hardoy chair butterfly chair by jorge ferrarihardoy cheaper imitations flooded the market knoll took legal action in  in the end losing theír claim of copyright infringement the model was dropped in  architecture preservationedit knoll sponsors exhibitions scholarships and other activities related to modernist architecture and design in  knoll and the world monuments fund a new yorkbased nonprofit organization launched modernism at risk an advocacy and conservation program modernism at risk encourages design solutions for at risk modernist buildings provides funding for conservation projects and raises awareness of the threats to modernist architecture through exhibitions and lectures the world monuments fundknoll modernism prize is awarded every two years to projects that preserve modernist architecture in  the first knoll modernism award was given to winfried brenne and franz jaschke of the german firm brenne gesellschaft von architekten for the restoration of the former adgb trade union school building on the outskirts of berlin the school built between  and  was a project of the bauhaus design school the architects were hannes meyer then director of the bauhaus and hans wittwer the  prize went to hubertjan henket and wessel de jonge the founders of docomomo international for the restoration of zonnestraal sanatorium estate in hilversum the netherlands the  prize was given to a consortium of japanese architects and academics for the restoration of the s hizuchi elementary school on shikoku island japan similar companiesedit ergocentric herman miller vitra furniture usm modular furniture lumiy referencesedit  httpw